comment: Domestic violence is no joke. People who go through it know how detrimental it can be and know that conveying details of abuse are not typically something they want to tell because there is a level of reliving the trauma that is humiliating and scary. The way AH conveys the details in her deposition is not typical. She is large with her gestures, bold in her mannerisms and words. She takes up vocal space and has a demeanor that doesn't show any shame, (not that victims SHOULD be ashamed, but it is a usual manifestation of relating a situation where they had no control) rather, she seems to be almost daring the listener not to sympathize with her ordeal. Her psychology, words, gestures, mannerisms, etc do not jive with her claims. She is PLAYING victim, she is not one with JD. I believe she has been abused in the past and probably enjoys the intensity of abuse, therefore, tried to introduce it to her relationship with JD, and she escalated when he didn't play. Sick, twisted, and smacks of a personality disorder.

comment:
Is it me, or is Amber Heard throwing everything at the wall just to see if anything sticks?  It is a well documented trait of Narcissists that they remember what they WANT to remember, but they have a convenient lapse of memory whenever it suits their narrative.  They are especially prone to forgetting anything that they have done that causes negative consequences.  When cornered by the complexities of their web of lies, they retreat behind "I disagree."  I'm sure her lawyer has coached her to simply make that statement, and STOP TALKING.  As we expected, Ms. Heard (like every other Narcissist) cannot keep her stories straight, and when confronted with her own, previous stories, or other witness testimony, defaults to "All the evidence is wrong, and I am right."  Is Ms. Heard unaware that it has been well documented that she recorded EVERYTHING?  Even Jerry Judge warns Ben King "Be careful Mate.  Even when she's in there--up in her room, she listens to you." which was caught on the Australia tape made by Ms. Heard HIDING her phone downstairs and retreating upstairs.  At the end of the tape, Ms. Heard retrieves her phone, while accidentally recording herself speaking to Mr. Judge about the hotel while still holding the phone.

      Dragged by the hair through broken glass...but in no need of medical assistance.  Ms. Heard RECORDED her Doctor, Dr. David Kipper, and her nurse, Debbie Lloyd, giving her Seroquel to calm her--but they don't treat the multiple injuries that she alleges she sustained?  They don't rush her to the hospital?  Is she saying Jerry Judge was there, and saw all these injuries, and did absolutely nothing?  In the tape that Ms. Heard recorded ON HER PHONE she can be heard saying through her sobbing  "Poor Johnny.  I love him.  I never meant to hurt him.  I didn't do it on purpose!",  "He needs me right now!  He needs me !",  "I'm sorry!  I'm sorry!"  Dr. Kipper says to the nurse "I'll tell you what's suddenly happening, with her.  This is guilt--this is--this is guilt."  Later Ms. Heard asks Mr. Judge "Did I do...this to the whole...floor?"  Jerry Judge is recorded saying "She admits to me she threw the first one--she threw a bottle at him.  She did it first."  Ms. Heard recorded the evidence that has come back to damn her.  When she listens to this recording, she plays it with her own internal narrative running through her mind.  She BELIEVES this tape confirms HER story.

     So...Ms. Heard saw Mr. Depp on the stairs, and thought about an unsubstantiated rumor she once heard, and without saying anything, punched Mr. Depp in the face, and now says, and I quote "And I remember this as it was the first incident where I ever struck him back."  Excuse me?  So...Mr. Depp was just standing on the stairs when you approached him and sucker punched him in the face...HE didn't punch YOU...so, how is this retaliatory?  If HE didn't punch anyone, YOU can't punch "him back"!  

     Kate Moss is on the record about Johnny Depp.  She referred to him as the ONLY partner who cared for her. "There's nobody that's ever really been able to take care of me.  Johnny did for a bit.  I believed what he said...Like if I said, 'What do I do?' He'd tell me.  And that's what I missed when I left.  I really lost that gauge of somebody I could trust.  Nightmare.  Years and years of crying.  Oh, the tears."  I hope that Ms. Moss DOES come forward and correct Ms. Heard's new tendency to put words in other people's mouths.
